cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about image super-resolution using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new training approach, which involves jointly training a deep network with a relatively shallow network, indicating a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning techniques for image super-resolution also suggests a possible connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its proposed method on widely adopted datasets, indicating a possible connection to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for upsampling in the latent feature space, which may suggest a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
